column1: # Name: Global Peace Index, Overall Score

# Definition: The overall Global Peace Index score measures the level of peace in a country. It is a weighted score of internal and external peace. Scores are from 1 to 5, with 1 being the most peaceful and 5 being the least peaceful.
# Source: Institute for Economics and Peace
# Data from the No Ceilings project: http://noceilings.org
# For more about the data, please visit http://noceilings.org/data
